<div class='communityQuestionAndAnswer'>
<div class='communityQuestion'>
<div class='questionText'>
<a href="/questions/1465478-how-christian-is-this-book-are-the-pagan">how Christian is this book? are the pagan Celts villainized?</a>
</div>
<div class='communityQAFooter questionFooter'>
<ul class='questionFooterActions'>
<li class='footerItem like'>
<span class='likeItContainer' id='like_container_community_question_1465478'><a id="like_count_community_question_1465478" rel="nofollow" href="/rating/voters/1465478?resource_type=CommunityQuestion"><span class="likesCount">4 likes</span></a>&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;<a rel="nofollow" class="jsLike like_it" href="https://www.goodreads.com/user/new?remember=true&amp;return_url=%2Fbook%2Fshow%2F73932.The_Paradise_War">like</a></span>

</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionTimestamp'>
<a href="/questions/1465478-how-christian-is-this-book-are-the-pagan">2 years ago</a>
</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionPermalink'>
<a href="/questions/1465478-how-christian-is-this-book-are-the-pagan">See all 2 answers</a>
</li>
</ul>
</div>

</div>
<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/105155307-tamara"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1573519116i/105155307._UY100_CR16,0,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/105155307-tamara">Tamara</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">Stephen Lawhead has written most of his books set in a Celtic world. He obviously loves the beautiful aspects of their culture, and makes his brand of<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">Stephen Lawhead has written most of his books set in a Celtic world. He obviously loves the beautiful aspects of their culture, and makes his brand of it wonderful and ennobling. He also mixes Christian and Celtic themes skillfully together, when those are included. He doesn't in any way villainize pagan Celts - I'm not really aware of any Celtic-based fantasy that does. <a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerFooter'>

